In Gallup's annual poll asking Americans to name the man they admire the most, Trump placed second to Obama in 2017 and 2018, tied with Obama for most admired man in 2019, and was named most admired in 2020.[750][751] Since Gallup started conducting the poll in 1948,[752] Trump is the first elected president not to be named most admired in his first year in office.[752]
